# The scripts in this folder illustrate the various forms
# allowed at each level of the language, defining separate
# scripts for the non-terminals which appear in the grammar
# rules to give to these examples a form close to the rules.

# Note: The examples are expected to run directly within their
# parent folder 'examples/grammar' which is referred as '.' and
# assigned to the PATH for the look-up of commands in the folder.
PATH=.

# A COMPLETE COMMAND IS:

# a list
list

# OR a list followed with the separator operator ';'
list;

# OR a list followed with the separator operator '&'
list&
